   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_SERVICENOW.PUB.ACTION.CREATE_RECORD

= General description =
This action is a generic action and can create a new record in any of the tables in ServiceNow. The user has to provide the table name for which new record 
has to create and the input fields. In case the user wants to link the newly created record with any other record, they can provide the system id as 
a parent ID for the new record.

= API Reference =
https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/orlando-application-development/page/integrate/inbound-rest/concept/c_TableAPI.html#r_TableAPI-POST

= Inputs =
* Parent System ID :   Provide System ID of the possible Parent record.
* Table Name*      :   Provide a table name to create the records.
* Fields*          :   Provide input in valid JSON format for new record E.g. {"State":"New","assignment_group":"Change Management","state": "New", "priority": "Medium"}

= Failure Conditions =
* If connection parameters are not correct.
* If the invalid table name is provided.
* If invalid JSON value provided in Fields parameter.

= Behavior = 
(none)

= Return Value =
&UC4RB_SN_SYS_ID#: system_id returned by ServiceNow
&UC4RB_SN_NUMBER#: number returned by ServiceNow

= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is non-zero in case of failure.

= Rollback =
(none)

= Logging =
Logs will be displayed in the AE report.

= Example =
Parent System ID : sdf89w3r4nf7w3r24un8374r5
Table Name       : change_request
Fields           : {"State":"New","assignment_group":"Change Management" ,"state": "New", "priority": "Medium"}
]]></Docu>
      </row>
   </documentation>
